msgSnippet: Hi, maybe I didn t get your message, but your aren t you asking us to review your *commercial product* without even offering some kind of free download to play
messageBody:
Hi,

maybe I didn't get your message, but your aren't you asking us to review
your *commercial product* without even offering some kind of free download
to play with? Are we getting somehow paid? What is your contribution to the
community?

Sorry if this message seems rude. Your message seemed rude to me also ;)

If I look at http://www.objecteering.com/produits51.htm, I see that
"generation of tests" isn't included in the free edition.

mathieu

----- Original Message -----
From: Eric Riou du Cosquer
To: junit@yahoogroups.com
Cc: Eric du Cosquer
Sent: Tuesday, March 05, 2002 12:41 PM
Subject: [junit] JUnit and UML...an MDA approach...


Hi all,

After a few months working on integrating JUnit in a UML case tool, I am
proud to present you my work!
The idea is to generate a test model from the application model and then to
modelize the test methods using UML sequence diagrams. Then the code is
automatically generated and executed in the JUnit framework!

Let's have a look a the pages describing this new approach and send me you
feedback in order to integrate new features in that work...and questions are
welcome,


Best regards,

Eric RIOU
